# Amux repository hygiene (T3 devops). NARROW by design: ignore generated and
# local-only artifacts, never canonical Guild evidence. `.guild/` holds the
# approved spec, plan, contexts, and receipts — it is DELIBERATELY NOT ignored.
# Volatile Guild indexes and event/log streams are local runtime artifacts;
# canonical plans, contexts, handoffs, run state, and receipts remain versioned.
/.guild/index.sqlite
/.guild/runs/current-run-id
/.guild/runs/**/logs/
/.guild/runs/**/events.ndjson
/.guild/runs/**/agent-bus/
/.guild/runs/**/evidence/
/.guild/team/*.current

# Built binaries left at the repo root by `go build -o amux ./cmd/amux` (and the
# amuxd companion). Release binaries live inside dist/ tarballs, never here.
/amux
/amuxd

# GoReleaser output tree and the completions staging tree it consumes.
/dist/
/build/

# Locally-installed pinned build-time tools (staticcheck, goreleaser, syft).
/.tools/

# Generated QA/security/soak/release evidence. `make clean` removes these; they
# are regenerated per run and must never enter git history. Both the repo-root
# tree and any package-relative tree (e.g. a nested harness run) are covered.
/.amux-artifacts/
**/.amux-artifacts/

# Coverage output (`make cover`).
/coverage.out

# Interrupted module/license integrity gates may leave these exact temporary
# snapshots behind. They are never source files.
/go.mod.bak
/go.sum.bak
/go.mod.lic-bak
/go.sum.lic-bak

# OS / editor residue.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
